            "title": "The One Concept You Need to Know to Strengthen Your Persuasion Skill",
            "summary": "By contrast, deductive reasoning is like a sculptor removing material until the artist reveals what she wishes to portray.\u201d Syllogistic Reasoning means the use of syllogisms to deduce arguments that draw conclusions from two premises\u2013a major one and a minor one. The most important piece of advice for improving your persuasion skills is to remain calm and keep a proper perspective at all times."
